Bob Tinsley (mauqx@csv.warwick.ac.uk) wrote:
: Quick question:
[on dealing with last short block in a block cipher]
: --Bob Tinsley   (mauqx@csv.warwick.ac.uk)

The trick is not to pad or increase length of text.  IBM's DES 
implementation uses the last full block for CFB on the last short block.
That is, DES(k,C[n-1]) XOR LAST_BYTES.  The extraneous bytes are thrown 
away. I think that by shifting to CFB mode any block cipher can be used 
without padding.  


